main_section_html: The best workout routine for true beginners is rather subjective to what the beginner is comfortable doing and their understanding of how to perform exercises. Their ultimate goal will also play a huge factor as well.Generally speaking though, beginners can start off performing anywhere between 2-4 workouts per week. These workouts can be either full body workouts or upper/lower workouts. The workouts will focus on learning ideal movement patterns of fundamental lifts such as Back Exercise , Chest Exercise , Leg Exercise.

main_section_html: As with our three-phase beginner’s program (which can also be used for a comeback after a layoff), even though you’re a bit more advanced now, a little downturn can do wonders for recovery. You don’t need to take a full week off from training, but a couple of days off or a week of low to medium intensity training with some extra recovery time should get you fully prepared to move into this program.Workout Plan include Shoulder Press , Back and Biceps , Chest and Triceps and legs
